# Create general function for data preparation of train and test data:

    # 1. Fill all null values with median of those values
    # 2. Create dummy variables for Location_ID, drop that column along with one of the dummy variable columns
    # 3. Make Atmospheric Pressure variables symmetric about their median (since they had normal curves)
    # 4. Create week, weekday and month variables
    # 5. Create dummy variables for weekday, drop that column along with one of the dummy variable columns
    # 6. Make month and week variables symmetric about their median (since they had normal curves)
    # 7. Create dummy variables for Park_ID, drop that column along with Park_ID = 19 column
    # 8. Create year column for train data
    # 9. Drop ID and Date columns

def prepare_data(df, is_train):
    df['Average_Breeze_Speed'].fillna(np.median(data['Average_Breeze_Speed'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Min_Breeze_Speed'].fillna(np.median(data['Min_Breeze_Speed'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Max_Breeze_Speed'].fillna(np.median(data['Max_Breeze_Speed'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Direction_Of_Wind'].fillna(np.median(data['Direction_Of_Wind'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    
    df_locations = pd.get_dummies(df['Location_Type'], prefix='location')
    df = pd.concat([df.drop(['Location_Type'], axis=1), df_locations], axis=1)
    df.drop(['location_4'], axis=1, inplace=True)
    
    df['Average_Atmospheric_Pressure'].fillna(np.median(data['Average_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Average_Atmospheric_Pressure'] = np.abs(df['Average_Atmospheric_Pressure'] - np.median(df['Average_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()))
    df['Max_Atmospheric_Pressure'].fillna(np.median(data['Max_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Max_Atmospheric_Pressure'] = np.abs(df['Max_Atmospheric_Pressure'] - np.median(df['Max_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()))
    df['Min_Atmospheric_Pressure'].fillna(np.median(data['Min_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['min_Atmospheric_Pressure'] = np.abs(df['Min_Atmospheric_Pressure'] - np.median(df['Min_Atmospheric_Pressure'].dropna()))
    
    df['Average_Moisture_In_Park'].fillna(np.median(data['Average_Moisture_In_Park'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Max_Moisture_In_Park'].fillna(np.median(data['Max_Moisture_In_Park'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Min_Moisture_In_Park'].fillna(np.median(data['Min_Moisture_In_Park'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    
    df['Max_Ambient_Pollution'].fillna(np.median(data['Max_Ambient_Pollution'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    df['Min_Ambient_Pollution'].fillna(np.median(data['Min_Ambient_Pollution'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    
    df['Var1'].fillna(np.median(data['Var1'].dropna()), inplace=True)
    
    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'], format='%d-%m-%Y')
    df['weekday'] = df['Date'].dt.dayofweek
    df_weekdays = pd.get_dummies(df['weekday'], prefix='weekday')
    df = pd.concat([df.drop(['weekday'], axis=1), df_weekdays], axis=1)
    df.drop(['weekday_0'], axis=1, inplace=True)
    df['week'] = df['Date'].dt.weekofyear
    df['week'] = np.abs(df['week'] - 31)
    df['month'] = df['Date'].dt.month
    df['month'] = np.abs(df['month'] - 7)
    
    df_parks = pd.get_dummies(df['Park_ID'], prefix='park')
    df = pd.concat([df.drop(['Park_ID'], axis=1), df_parks], axis=1)
    
    if is_train:
        df['year'] = df['Date'].dt.year
        df.drop(['park_19'], axis=1, inplace=True)
    return df.drop(['ID', 'Date'], axis=1)

x_test = train[train['year'] >= 2001].drop(['Footfall'], axis=1)
y_test = train[train['year'] >= 2001]['Footfall']

x_test.drop(['year'], axis=1, inplace=True)
xgb.fit(x_train, y_train)

Ending Notes¶

Since I was unable to participate in the competition actively for a major chunk of the time due to personal engagements, there are many things that I had in mind but was unable to do.

Here are some ideas that I tried, but didn't fructify:

  1. Create separate variables Speed_x (cosine) and Speed_y (sine) for all Breeze Speed variables, and dropped all of them along with Direction of Wind.
  2. Separate models for months [1,2,3,4,11,12] and [5,6,7,8,9,10]. The Footfall values in these months had significant difference in mean.
  3. RandomForestRegressor and XGBoost with GridSearchCV for hyperparameter tuning.
  4. Create ensembles for various solution files.
  5. Feature normalization

Here are some ideas that I thought of, but was unable to implement:

  1. Figure out Var1. The graph for Footfall vs. Var1 showed a somewhat discrete trend. Could've explored that further.
  2. Improve on the missing value imputation. My model was intended as a very simple, initial model with all median values for missing ones. I could've used more sophisticated techniques, since a large part of the data was missing. Imputations based on Location_ID, Park_ID, Month, etc. (or a combination of many) might've yielded better results.
  3. Proper feature normalization that could've yielded better results.
  4. Create bins for months, and weeks.
  5. Use time series modelling techniques like exponential smoothing, rolling mean or moving average to get better results.
  6. Tune the model properly.
